==Education==
The following schools are located in Guayanilla and students from both schools have participated in the Rose Parade in California on several occasions:
* Escuela Arístides Cales Quirós 
* Asunción Rodríguez de Sala

==Transportation==
There are 35 bridges in Guayanilla.

==Nazario Collection==
The Nazario Collection, a set of inscribed stones discovered by Catholic priest and amateur archeologist José M. Nazario (and which popular culture links to Taíno chief Agüeybaná II), has become a cultural symbol for the municipality. The statuettes serve as the center piece of Guayanilla&#x27;s Father Nazario Museum of Lithic Epigraphy.

